  "text": "First, we split the theorems into separate conjuncts even when they appear under quantifiers. Each conjunct can be considered as separate theorems from this point. We then rewrite every theorem statement to conjunctive normal forms. In this normalization we assume classical logic, however if this is not desired, it is possible to consider intuitionistic clausification [CITATION_1] . As the focus is on proof libraries that can be expressed in type theory, we preserve the equivalences ⇔ and consider them as equalities between propositions.",
